  "text": "airpods Sign in to your Android Police account Summary Apple is reportedly bringing a live-translation feature to AirPods. The feature will allow real-time translated conversations between speakers of different languages. Google Pixel Buds have offered a similar live-translation feature since the first-gen launch in 2017. Android and iOS have a long history of borrowing features from each other, though it often feels like Android does more of the copying. Recently, Google decided to bring back lock screen widgets after seeing their success on iOS, but now it looks like Apple might be taking inspiration from one of the best Google Pixel Buds features for its AirPods. Related According to Bloomberg, Apple is working on a live translation feature for AirPods, set to arrive later this year via a software update. The feature won't reportedly be limited to new AirPods models — it will also roll out to some existing AirPods (though it's unclear which ones). It's expected to launch alongside iOS 19 and would allow users speaking different languages to have real-time, in-person translated conversations. Here's how it will reportedly work: imagine two people speaking different languages — one in English and the other in Spanish. The iPhone would listen to the Spanish speaker, translate the speech, and relay it in English to the person wearing AirPods. The phone would then listen to the AirPods user, translate their response into Spanish, and play it aloud through the iPhone's speaker. Live translation could be coming to AirPods later this year If that sounds familiar, it's because Google Pixel Buds have offered this exact feature since their first-gen launch in 2017. Pixel Buds have offered live translation for years, working in a nearly identical way using the Google Translate app. Users can trigger it with \"Hey Google\" and say \"Help me speak \", launching conversation mode in Google Translate, which currently supports 40 languages. Related In fact, Google Pixel Buds offer an additional feature called Transcribe Mode, which listens to another language in real-time and displays live transcriptions while translating. While it's unclear whether Apple's implementation will match Google's full feature set, it's still great to see one of the best Pixel Buds features potentially coming to AirPods. Apple AirPods 4 (with Active Noise Cancellation) $149 $179 Save $30 Apple's AirPods 4 offer a balance of awareness and noise cancelation at a lower price than the AirPods Pro lineup. They provide up to 30 hours of battery life with the fully charged USB-C case and come with an IP54 rating for dust and sweat resistance.",
