rent languages.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n                    \u003cli\u003e\n                                        Google Pixel Buds have offered a similar live-translation feature since the first-gen launch in 2017.\n                        \u003c/li\u003e\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n    \n        \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\nAndroid and iOS have a long history of \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/ios-18-app-locking-system-dark-home-screen-icons/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eborrowing features from each other\u003c/a\u003e, though it often feels like Android does more of the copying. Recently, Google decided to     \n\n        \n\u003cspan data-id=\"1025794\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-lock-screen-widgets-aosp-android-16-qpr1/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebring back lock screen widgets\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n after seeing their success on iOS, but now it looks like Apple might be taking inspiration from one of the best Google Pixel Buds features for its AirPods.    \u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"1524-40dc-aeeb20799099\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/apple-airpods-4-anc-review/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"3190\" height=\"1794\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A photograph of Apple\u0026#39;s Airpods 4, with the case open\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/airpods-4-beauty.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAccording to \u003ca href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-03-13/apple-plans-ios-19-feature-that-lets-airpods-live-translate-conversations\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBloomberg\u003c/a\u003e, Apple is working on a live translation feature for AirPods, set to arrive later this year via a software update. The feature won\u0026#39;t reportedly be limited to new AirPods models — it will also roll out to some existing AirPods (though it\u0026#39;s unclear which ones). It\u0026#39;s expected to launch alongside iOS 19 and would allow users speaking different languages to have real-time, in-person translated conversations.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eHere\u0026#39;s how it will reportedly work: imagine two people speaking different languages — one in English and the other in Spanish. The iPhone would listen to the Spanish speaker, translate the speech, and relay it in English to the person wearing AirPods. The phone would then listen to the AirPods user, translate their response into Spanish, and play it aloud through the iPhone\u0026#39;s speaker.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"live-translation-could-be-coming-to-airpods-later-this-year\"\u003e\n                        Live translation could be coming to AirPods later this year\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eIf that sounds familiar, it\u0026#39;s because \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-pixel-buds-pro-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eGoogle Pixel Buds\u003c/a\u003e have offered this exact feature since their first-gen launch in 2017. Pixel Buds have offered live translation for years, working in a nearly identical way using the Google Translate app. Users can trigger it with \u0026#34;Hey Google\u0026#34; and say \u0026#34;Help me speak \u003clanguage\u003e\u0026#34;, launching conversation mode in Google Translate, which currently supports 40 languages.\u003c/language\u003e\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                                    \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"5c5d-4057-99ddee4bd15e\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-pixel-buds-real-time-translation/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/google-pixel-buds-pro-2-solo-2.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/google-pixel-buds-pro-2-solo-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-con